channel.title: Guys/Girls, Look
channel.description:
Well, everyone, I've noticed a lot of you have started "disliking me" because I am in-mature. Well I have no idea why, but as soon as I turned 13, I for some reason, somewhat became in-mature. I just read MybJames' post, about how I've gone from being mature to a whiny bitch. Well, I never really looked at myself until that moment, which led me to write this topic. I've been having little "arguments" with Mr. Chris, and, basically I'm sorry about that.
I have no idea why, but pretty much the day I turned 13. I became awfully in-mature. I guess what I mean is I probably started life's cycle of puberty.. :( I don't enjoy arguing with you all and I sure as hell don't enjoy being hated by you. The way I see it, the stronger man is always the man who says sorry and moves on. And the weaker man is the person who says "HAHAHA I'm not figiving you." That sounded like something I would say...
Until this moment, I'm going to try and be "un-imature"... Because it's not only on these forums that I have been acting this way, I have been in real life.. Before I used to take my racing incredibly serious. Now all I want to do is hang around the girls and all the hormonious activities.
So, I guess what I am trying to say is, can I please have another chance and not be an idiot? And that I'm terribably sorry to Mr. Chris and all the people I was an asshole too.
Man, puberties a bitch.
